          %input#amount{:name => "amount", :type => "text", :value => "10"}
        %div
          %input{:type => "submit", :value => "Show"}
    %h2 What?
    :markdown
      A site for auto-refreshing the [Twitter](http://twitter.com) [hashtag](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hashtag#Hash_tags) for your event.
    %h2 How?
    :markdown
      Just type in the hashtag and the amount of tweets you're willing to see at once on the form above and press Show. Or... type in your browser's location bar [http://hashfresh.heroku.com/twitter/YOUR_HASHTAG](http://hashfresh.heroku.com/twitter/hashtag).
    %h2 Why?
    :markdown
      I went to a conference, where there was a screen displaying the [Twitter search page](http://twitter.com/#search?q=%23hashtag") for the conference's hashtag. The Twitter page contains too much unnecessary stuff and doesn't auto-refresh so I had to fix it.
